        <page n="01" image="va.au.rv.1863.10.16.01">
            <pageNote>On this page are a reprinted list of deserters from the 52nd Regiment of the
                Virginia Volunteers, Governor Letcher's proclamation calling for the formation of
                volunteer companies for local protection, proceedings of the General Assembly, war
                news, and advertisements.</pageNote>
        </page>
        <page n="02" image="va.au.rv.1863.10.16.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Virginia</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Virginia "has not abated a jot or a tittle in her devotion to the cause she
                    has espoused, but has rather increased its intensity as her acts will eminently
                    prove."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The editor writes about the commitment to the Confederate cause evident in
                    the actions and sacrifices of Virginians.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look>**</look>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>G. W. Summers</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>George W. Summers of Kanawha has announced that he is a candidate for the
                    next United States Congress from northwestern Virginia. The editor calls him "an
                    able and talented statesman" who once would have been a good prospect for the
                    governorship of Virginia. His action in aligning himself with the traitorous
                    government of the breakaway section of Virginia, however, disappoints the editor
                    and proves that Summers's true allegiance is not to Virginia.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
